SIMD help to divide the load between cores in one CPU unit. Thus, enoming time because the cores share the same register and same instruction set.
And if you combine it with multithreading you get an even better result.  


The algorithm for all task as similar.

1) Scalar approach:
  Simply go one by one on each character and count
2) SIMD approach:
  create 4 units to execute 32 characters simmultaniously.
3) Multithreading approach:
  Split the string in  parts(4 equal parts of equal length), then pas each one to one of 4 threads.
4) Multithreading+SIMD approach:
  do the same thing as in multithreading approach, but each thread creates units of its own to analyze 32 characters at the same time.

